All the videos on this channel are uploaded with full digital copyrights either owned by OSR Digital or officially provided by different content owners. If there are any copyright issues with the uploaded videos, please feel free to contact us to resolve the matter and avoid conflicts.

snippet.title: Saraswati Mantra | Om Saraswati Namo Namah | Saraswati Vandana | Saraswati Puja | Master Your Mind
snippet.description:
Experience the divine power of the Saraswati Mantra, a sacred Vedic chant dedicated to Goddess Saraswati‚Äîthe eternal source of wisdom, intelligence, creativity, and clarity of thought. This mantra is traditionally known to enhance learning, focus, communication skills, and decision-making abilities, which are essential foundations for achieving success in modern life, including career growth, financial planning, and wealth creation.

In today‚Äôs fast-paced world of technology, luxury lifestyle, high-performance careers, and global financial markets, mental clarity and disciplined thinking are more valuable than ever. Regular listening to the Saraswati Mantra helps calm the mind, sharpen analytical skills, and align your thoughts toward positive outcomes. A focused mind is crucial for excelling in investment strategies, stock market analysis, business leadership, entrepreneurship, and long-term financial stability.

Many successful individuals across the world believe that spiritual discipline complements material growth. When your mind is balanced, you make wiser choices‚Äîwhether it‚Äôs related to personal finance, wealth management, real estate investment, or building assets that support a premium lifestyle. Listening to this mantra during meditation, work, or study can support better concentration, improved productivity, and confident communication‚Äîskills valued in corporate careers, high-income professions, and global businesses.

This devotional audio is ideal for those aspiring to grow in financial wealth, career success, and intellectual excellence, while remaining spiritually grounded. It resonates strongly with audiences interested in luxury cars, automobiles, high-end brands, financial freedom, passive income, and smart money habits. A calm and intelligent mindset also supports better judgment when dealing with banking, insurance, mutual funds, cryptocurrency awareness, and international investments.

Listening to the Saraswati Mantra daily can inspire discipline, creativity, and confidence‚Äîqualities that align naturally with success in business growth, startup ecosystems, digital marketing, global employment opportunities, and lifestyle goals. Whether you are a student, professional, entrepreneur, or investor, this mantra helps cultivate inner strength that supports both spiritual peace and material progress.

üå∏ Listen with devotion
üå∏ Chant along or play during work or meditation
üå∏ Maintain a positive intention for knowledge, growth, and prosperity

May Goddess Saraswati bless you with wisdom that leads to meaningful success, balanced wealth, and a fulfilled life

Title :- Saraswati Mantra
Singer, Composition, Lyrics :- Sohini mishra

This mantra is traditionally known to enhance learning, focus, communication skills, and decision-making abilities, which are essential foundations for achieving success in modern life, including career growth, financial planning, and wealth creation.

In today‚Äôs fast-paced world of technology, luxury lifestyle, high-performance careers, and global financial markets, mental clarity and disciplined thinking are more valuable than ever. A focused mind is crucial for excelling in investment strategies, stock market analysis, business leadership, entrepreneurship, and long-term financial stability.

Many successful individuals across the world believe that spiritual discipline complements material growth. When your mind is balanced, you make wiser choices‚Äîwhether it‚Äôs related to personal finance, wealth management, real estate investment, or building assets that support a premium lifestyle. This devotional audio is ideal for those aspiring to grow in financial wealth, career success, and intellectual excellence, while remaining spiritually grounded. snippet.title: Vadh 2 - Official Trailer | Sanjay Mishra, Neena Gupta | Jaspal Singh Sandhu | Luv Films | 6th Feb
snippet.description:
An old prison guard- Shambhunath Mishra (Sanjay Mishra) and a jail inmate- Manju Singh (Neena Gupta) share a bond forged behind prison walls. 

When their ordinary lives are pulled into a moral conflict and truth refuses to surface, they stand at the centre of a choice that has consequences.

#Vadh2 #SanjayMishra #NeenaGupta

A Luv Films presentation, Vadh 2 is written and directed by Jaspal Singh Sandhu and produced by Luv Ranjan and Ankur Garg. The film is slated for a theatrical release on 6th February 2026.

Starring: Sanjay Mishra, Neena Gupta with Kumud Mishra, Amitt K. Singh, Akshay Dogra, Shilpa Shukla & Yogita Bihani
Written & Directed By: Jaspal Singh Sandhu
Produced By: Luv Ranjan & Ankur Garg

Yoon Tera Hoon, Tu Dard De To Dard Ko Bhi Choom Loon
Muskuraana Hai Tujhi Se Tujhse hi Aaraam hai
Tu Nahi To Main Nahi Hoon
Zindagi Tere Naam Hai
Tu Na To Main Bemaaine
Hona Mera Hi Fizool Hai
Koi Shart Ho Ya Dard Ho
Yeh Raabta Qubool Hai
 
Hai Ishq Mein Jab Doobe Hum
Gham Bhi Mile To Kaisa Gham
Tera Sahi Tera Ghalat
Tera Jhooth Bhi To Qubool Hai

Mahboob Hota Hai Khuda
Yahi Ishq Ka To Usool Hai

Experience a fresh take on the timeless Nepali folk classic, "Allare Nani Kesi." Originally composed and sung by the legendary Jhalakman Gandharva, this remake version is beautifully reimagined by Yubaraj Portel only on Music Nepal's Official YouTube Channel.

This version brings modern production while keeping the soulful essence of the Sarangi and the traditional Gandharva roots alive for a new generation.

"‡§Ö‡§≤‡•ç‡§≤‡§æ‡§∞‡•á ‡§®‡§æ‡§®‡•Ä" (Allare Nani Kesi) ‡§è‡§â‡§ü‡§æ ‡§ï‡§æ‡§≤‡§ú‡§Ø‡•Ä ‡§®‡•á‡§™‡§æ‡§≤‡•Ä ‡§≤‡•ã‡§ï ‡§ó‡•Ä‡§§ ‡§π‡•ã‡•§  ‡§Ø‡•Å‡§µ‡§∞‡§æ‡§ú ‡§™‡•ã‡§∞‡•ç‡§ü‡•á‡§≤‡§ï‡•ã ‡§∞‡§ø‡§Æ‡•á‡§ï ‡§∏‡§Ç‡§∏‡•ç‡§ï‡§∞‡§£ ‡§∞ ‡§ù‡§≤‡§ï‡§Æ‡§æ‡§® ‡§ó‡§®‡•ç‡§ß‡§∞‡•ç‡§µ‡§ï‡•ã ‡§Æ‡•å‡§≤‡§ø‡§ï (Original) ‡§∏‡§Ç‡§∏‡•ç‡§ï‡§∞‡§£‡§Æ‡§æ,

This folk melody reflects the culture, tradition, and heartfelt emotions of Nepali villages. A perfect combination of soulful lyrics, traditional instruments, and rhythmic beats.
Enjoy the real taste of Nepali Lok Geet Dohori and regional music heritage. Celebrate the spirit of Nepal through Music Nepal‚Äôs timeless Lok Geet collection, bringing together authentic Nepali folk sounds. Experience soulful traditional music with rich melodies and heartfelt folk emotions.  A beautiful blend of lok dohori and classic traditional rhythms that portray love, devotion, culture, and village life.

snippet.title: Diwana Hai Ye Man (Lyrical Video) | Sonu Nigam | Alka Yagnik Anu Malik | Chori Chori Chupke Chupke
snippet.description:
"Diwana Hai Ye Man" from the film Chori Chori Chupke Chupke is a melodious romantic track sung by Sonu Nigam and Alka Yagnik, with music composed by Anu Malik. Featuring Salman Khan and Rani Mukerji, the song captures the fluttering emotions of love, innocence, and heartfelt longing. With its soothing melody, expressive vocals, and early-2000s Bollywood charm, this track remains a memorable and evergreen romantic favorite. 

Credits: 
Singer: Sonu Nigam, Alka Yagnik
Music: Anu Malik
Lyrics: Sameer
Movie: Chori Chori Chupke Chupke
Starring: Salman Khan, Rani Mukerji
Director: Abbas Mustan
Producer: Nazim Rizvi
Label: Universal Music India

Lyrics: 

Deewana Hain Yeh Man Kyon Pagal Hai Dhadkan 

Kyon Tujhpe Mujhe Pyaar Aaya Hai 

Yeh Mausam Kyon Saje Yeh Payal Kyon Baje 

Yeh Kaisa Khumar Chhaya Hai 

Koi Bata De Koi Bata De Koi Bataye Na 

Yeh Main Janoon Ya Tu Jaane 

Is Baat Ko Koi Kya Jaane 

Dil Tera Mera Dil Jhoome Re Jhoome 

Dil Tera Mera Dil Jhoome Re Jhoome 

Maine Teri Dhadkanon Pe Sanam 

Apni Wafa Ki Kahani Likhi 

Maine Tere Naam Jaan-e-Jigar 

Apni Haseen Zindagani Likhi 

Yeh Kajal Kyon Hase, Yeh Naina Kyon Jhuke 

Yeh Kaisa Nikhar Mujhpe Aaya Hain 

Koi Bata De Koi Bata De Koi Bataye Na 

Yeh Main Janoon Ya Tu Jaane 

Is Baat Ko Koi Kya Jaane 

Dil Tera Mera Dil Jhoome Re Jhoome 

Dil Tera Mera Dil Jhoome Re Jhoome 

O Mere Rabba Tera Shukriya 

Jo Maine Maanga Mujhe Mil Gaya 

Meri Mohabbat Asar Kar Gayi 

Khwabon Ka Mehka Chaman Khil Gaya 

Yeh Bandhan Kyon Bandhe, Yeh Rishte Kyon Jude 

Yeh Mausam Kya Sandesha Laaya Hai 

Koi Bata De Koi Bata De Koi Bataye Na 

Yeh Main Janoon Ya Tu Jaane 

Is Baat Ko Koi Kya Jaane 

Deewana Hain Yeh Man Kyon Pagal Hai Dhadkan 

Kyon Tujhpe Mujhe Pyaar Aaya Hai 

Yeh Mausam Kyon Saje Yeh Payal Kyon Baje 

Yeh Kaisa Khumar Chhaya Hai 

Koi Bata De Koi Bata De Koi Bataye Na 

Yeh Main Janoon Ya Tu Jaane 

Is Baat Ko Koi Kya Jaane 

Dil Tera Mera Dil Jhoome Re Jhoome 

Dil Tera Mera Dil Jhoome Re Jhoome

snippet.title: [Hindi] BGIS 2026 THE GRIND | Week 3 | Day 3
snippet.description:
Week 3 of The Grind is underway, and the race is starting to take real shape. With multiple weeks of action behind them, teams now know exactly where they stand. Every decision, every rotation, and every fight matters more than ever as the competition intensifies.

Group A:
iQOO ORANGUTAN
K9 Esports
iQOOSOUL
Infinix TrueRippers
Nebula Esports
OnePlus Gods Reign
Higgboson Esports
Madkings
iQOO RECKONING ESPORTS
iQOO8BIT
Team AX
Victores Sumus
Hero Xtreme Godlike
RAPID CHAOS ESPORTS
Blitz Esports
Autobotz Esports

Group B:
GENESIS ESPORTS
The Vanguard
Rising Esports
TWOB
EVOX Esports
Zutsu Esports
Wyld Fangs
SINEWY ESPORTS
4TR Official
NoNx Esports
TEAM X ESPORTS
LASTADE ESPORTS
The Knight Mobs
KALINGA ESPORTS
iQOO Team Tamilas
Team H4K

Expect high-pressure gameplay, sharper strategies, and moments that can shift the leaderboard in an instant. Whether teams are pushing to stay on top or fighting their way back into contention, this is where consistency and composure are truly tested.
Tune in, support your favourite teams, and watch the next chapter of BGIS 2026 unfold live.

Registrations for Rising Star 2026 are now open: https://bit.ly/RisingStar2026
Follow us on Instagram: https://instagram.com/KraftonIndiaEsports

About "Lamjung Daadaama Hawa Sarara"
"Lamjung Daadaama Hawa Sarara" is a popular Nepali folk song that originates from the Lamjung district of Nepal. It is a lively and upbeat song that is typically sung and danced to during festivals and social gatherings.

The lyrics of the song are in the Nepali language and describe the beauty of the Lamjung district's natural scenery, including the mountains, rivers, and forests. The song also celebrates the joy and happiness of the people living in Lamjung and their culture and traditions.

The musical arrangement of "Lamjung Daadaama Hawa Sarara" typically features traditional Nepali instruments such as the madal (a type of drum), tungna (a stringed instrument), and sarangi (a bowed instrument). The song has a catchy melody and rhythm that are easy to dance along to.

Over time, "Lamjung Daadaama Hawa Sarara" has become a beloved Nepali folk song that is popular across the country and is often performed by musicians and dancers at cultural events and festivals.

About "Lamjung Daadaama Hawa Sarara"
"Lamjung Daadaama Hawa Sarara" is a popular Nepali folk song that originates from the Lamjung district of Nepal. It is a lively and upbeat song that is typically sung and danced to during festivals and social gatherings.

The lyrics of the song are in the Nepali language and describe the beauty of the Lamjung district's natural scenery, including the mountains, rivers, and forests. The song also celebrates the joy and happiness of the people living in Lamjung and their culture and traditions.

The musical arrangement of "Lamjung Daadaama Hawa Sarara" typically features traditional Nepali instruments such as the madal (a type of drum), tungna (a stringed instrument), and sarangi (a bowed instrument). The song has a catchy melody and rhythm that are easy to dance along to.

Over time, "Lamjung Daadaama Hawa Sarara" has become a beloved Nepali folk song that is popular across the country and is often performed by musicians and dancers at cultural events and festivals.

About "Lamjung Daadaama Hawa Sarara"
"Lamjung Daadaama Hawa Sarara" is a popular Nepali folk song that originates from the Lamjung district of Nepal. It is a lively and upbeat song that is typically sung and danced to during festivals and social gatherings.

The lyrics of the song are in the Nepali language and describe the beauty of the Lamjung district's natural scenery, including the mountains, rivers, and forests. The song also celebrates the joy and happiness of the people living in Lamjung and their culture and traditions.

The musical arrangement of "Lamjung Daadaama Hawa Sarara" typically features traditional Nepali instruments such as the madal (a type of drum), tungna (a stringed instrument), and sarangi (a bowed instrument). The song has a catchy melody and rhythm that are easy to dance along to.

Over time, "Lamjung Daadaama Hawa Sarara" has become a beloved Nepali folk song that is popular across the country and is often performed by musicians and dancers at cultural events and festivals.

snippet.title: 1 Million Vs 1 Million Gems Pack Opening! We Packed 13x 117 Rated TOTY
snippet.description:
The Ultimate Pack Opening Battle is here! RK Reddy vs De Mysterio. The rules are simple: 116 OVR = 1 Point, 117 OVR = 2 Points. The loser has to DISCARD a 117 OVR Player!

In this video, I invite De Mysterio to my channel for a massive TOTY Pack Opening showdown. We open hundreds of Draft Packs simultaneously to see who has the better luck. It was an insane battle that went down to the final pack, resulting in a 9-9 DRAW!

But there can only be one winner... so I enforced a "Tie-Breaker Rule" based on who packed the most 117s. Did I win? Or did De Mysterio have to discard his 117 Zico? Watch until the end to find out!

Rules: 116 OVR (1 Pt) vs 117 OVR (2 Pts) üìù

My Packs: Pulling 117 Mbappe & 117 Vitinha!
